{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Smart item group/ungroup\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Thanks to daxliniere for the following specification:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab I select 3 ungrouped items and run the action - those items form a unique group.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If I run the action again those 3 are no longer part of any group.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If I select 3 items, some of which are part of a group and some ungrouped, the ungrouped items should be placed into the existing group.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab If I select 3 items, some of which are part of one group and some another group, the grouping should be removed.\sa180\par}
}

