{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 MIDI Event Editor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 One-line MIDI event editor\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Math Operators ()+, -, *, /) can be used to calculate relative values, also on multi-selected values.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The Range Operator (.) can be used to scale a selection from its current range to the specified target range (for example: .20-80 will scale the selected events to the range 20-80).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When setting negative absolute values for pitch bend, use --VALUE (instead of -VALUE, which will use the '-' Math Operator)\par}
}

